\subsection{Scaling Behavior}

The Fibonacci method exhibits logarithmic scaling:

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Small multipliers ($< 100$):} $\sim 2$--$5$ Fibonacci terms, $\sim 22$--$50$ ms
    \item \textbf{Medium multipliers ($100$--$10{,}000$):} $\sim 3$--$7$ terms, $\sim 50$--$70$ ms
    \item \textbf{Large multipliers ($10{,}000$--$1{,}000{,}000$):} $\sim 5$--$10$ terms, $\sim 70$--$110$ ms
\end{itemize}

The sub-linear scaling is a direct consequence of $\mathcal{O}(\log_\phi n)$ Zeckendorf decomposition.

